      "content": "To calculate the total impedance ($Z$) in a series RL circuit, you need to use the formula: $Z = \\sqrt{R^2 + X_L^2}$. Here, $R$ is the resistance (50 ohms) and $X_L$ is the inductive reactance (30 ohms). Plug in your values and calculate the square root of the sum of the squares of these two components. This will give you the total opposition to the current in the circuit.",
